ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: AASPIRE Participant Type / Version Administered
Notes: 1= Direct Report (DR); 2= Direct Report - Supported (DR-S); 3= Caregiver Report (CR)

ElementDescription: Do (Direct Report: you / Caregiver Report: they) currently get developmental disability services? These are for people with developmental disabilities including autism, intellectual disability, cerebral palsy, epilepsy, and other related conditions. They usually give (you/them) a case manager, a personal agent (PA), or service coordinator. Examples of things DD services could give (you/them) or pay for might include case management/having a case manager, program planning to develop an Individual Program Plan, evaluations, help getting connected to other services, work programs, transportation, residential services, nursing/home aid services, behavioral intervention, respite)
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 2= I do not know

ElementDescription: Do (Direct Report: you / Caregiver Report: they) get most of (your/their) developmental disability services from the same agency that provides (your/their) service coordination?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 2= I do not know

ElementDescription: What is the name of the agency or program that (Direct Report: you get most of your / Caregiver Report: they get most of their) developmental disability services from?

Where do (Direct Report: you / Caregiver Report: they) get developmental disability services? (Check all that apply): A government agency (e.g., your/their county developmental disability program or a regional center)

Where do (Direct Report: you / Caregiver Report: they) get developmental disability services? (Check all that apply): A private organization, a non-profit, or another non-government agency (e.g., the ARC or a program you/they and your/their family pays for)
Where do (Direct Report: you / Caregiver Report: they) get developmental disability services? (Check all that apply): Somewhere else
Where do (Direct Report: you / Caregiver Report: they) get developmental disability services? (Check all that apply): I do not know
Do (Direct Report: you need / Caregiver Report: you think they need) developmental disability services?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes, and (Direct Report: I am / Caregiver Report: they are) on a waitlist to get services; 2= Yes, but (I am/they are) not eligible for services; 3= Yes, but the services (I/they) need are not available; 4= Yes, but (I/they) have not been able to get them for another reason; 5= I do not know
